{"data":{"npm":{"manifest":{"name":"@financial-times/x-node-jsx","version":"0.0.0","description":"This module extends Node's require function to enable the use of .jsx files at runtime.","main":"src/index.js","keywords":["x-dash"],"author":"","license":"ISC","dependencies":{"pirates":"^4.0.0","sucrase":"^3.6.0"},"repository":{"type":"git","url":"https://github.com/Financial-Times/x-dash.git"},"homepage":"https://github.com/Financial-Times/x-dash/tree/master/packages/x-node-jsx","engines":{"node":">= 8.0.0"},"publishConfig":{"access":"public"}}},"markdown":{"html":"<h1 id=\"x-node-jsx\"><a href=\"#x-node-jsx\" aria-label=\"x node jsx permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>x-node-jsx</h1>\n<p>This module extends Node's <code class=\"language-text\">require()</code> function to enable the use of <code class=\"language-text\">.jsx</code> files at runtime. It uses <a href=\"https://github.com/ariporad/pirates\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Pirates</a> to safely add a require hook and <a href=\"https://github.com/alangpierce/sucrase\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Sucrase</a> to transform code on-the-fly.</p>\n<h2 id=\"installation\"><a href=\"#installation\" aria-label=\"installation permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Installation</h2>\n<p>This module is compatible with Node 8+ and is distributed on npm.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> -S @financial-times/x-node-jsx</code></pre></div>\n<p>To add the require hook you only need to import the register module. You can do this programmatically in your application code:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'@financial-times/x-node-jsx/register'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Or use the <code class=\"language-text\">--require</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">-r</code> flag when invoking Node:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">node --require <span class=\"token string\">\"@financial-times/x-node-jsx/register\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>You can also add the require hook manually. This will return a function which can be used to later remove the hook:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> addHook <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'@financial-times/x-node-jsx'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> removeHook <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">addHook</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Some time later...</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">removeHook</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>An options object may also be provided, the options and their defaults are shown below:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> addHook <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'@financial-times/x-node-jsx'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">addHook</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\tproduction<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\ttransforms<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">'imports'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'jsx'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>These options will be passed to the Sucrase module. To see more options take a look at the <a href=\"https://github.com/alangpierce/sucrase#transforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Sucrase documentation</a>.</p>\n<p>After the hook has been added <code class=\"language-text\">.jsx</code> files can be imported and will be transformed on-the-fly:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Add the hook</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'@financial-times/x-node-jsx/register'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Transparently require .jsx files</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> App <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'./components/App.jsx'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>","headings":[{"value":"x-node-jsx","depth":1},{"value":"Installation","depth":2}]},"storybook":null,"modules":{"edges":[{"node":{"path":"/packages/x-engine","context":{"title":"x-engine"}}},{"node":{"path":"/packages/x-handlebars","context":{"title":"x-handlebars"}}},{"node":{"path":"/packages/x-node-jsx","context":{"title":"x-node-jsx"}}}]}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"type":"npm-package-packages","title":"x-node-jsx","source":"packages","packageName":"@financial-times/x-node-jsx","packageDescription":"This module extends Node's require function to enable the use of .jsx files at runtime.","storiesPath":"/packages/x-node-jsx/stories","packagePath":"/packages/x-node-jsx/package","readmePath":"/packages/x-node-jsx/readme"}}